The paper discusses the use of immersive virtual- and augmented-reality headsets for data visualization, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also focuses on spatial encodings for flow maps, which involves graphics (cs.GR), geometric modeling (cs.GI), and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. Additionally, the paper explores the use of interactive designs for flow maps, which can be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI).
